      • subList

        public RangedList<T> subList(long begin,
                             long end)
        Description copied from interface: RangedList
        Provides a RangedList of the elements contained in this object from index begin to index end.

        If the provided range exceeds the indices contained in this instance (i.e. if begin is lower than the lowest index contained in this instance, or if end is higher than the highest index contained in this instance) the method will return the elements it contains that fit within the provided range.

        Specified by:
        subList in interface RangedList<T>
        Parameters:
        begin - starting index of the desired sub-list
        end - last index of the desired sub-list (exlusive)
        Returns:
        a ranged list of the elements contained in this RangedList that fit in the provided range.
